      • getAsync

        @NonNull
 @CheckResult(suggest="IAltFuture#fork()")
public <T> IAltFuture<T,okhttp3.Response> getAsync()
        Take the output from the previous step in the chain as the URL.

        Note that the input object has T#toString() is called to generate the URL at the last possible moment before the network connection is opened. This may be useful to delay the decision of which URL will be used, for example to decide what is the highest priority use of the network at that moment.

        Type Parameters:
        T - the output of the upchain step
        Returns:
        alt future of the network response
